g.text: When to use and when not to use Machine Learning
Machine Learning is a powerful tool for solving practical problems.
However, like any tool, it should be used in the right context.
When to use it
When not to use it
The problem is too complex or big for coding
and only a partial solution is viable
Spam Detection, so many rules!
The problem is constantly changing
Scraping specific elements from dynamic webpages
The problem is perceptive
Speech, Image, and Video recognition
The phenomenon is unstudied
Personalized mental health medication options
based on the patient's genetic and sensory data
The problem has a simple objective
Yes/No decision or single number
It is cost effective to use it
Every action of the system has
to be explainable
Every change in the system when compared to its previous
version has to be explainable
The cost of error made by the system is too high
We want to get to the market asap
A simple heuristic would work reasonably well
